<P>
Eddie Munster Arrested: Patrick Allan Lilley, who portrayed the werewolf-like 
boy Eddie in the 1960s television comedy "The Munsters," has been charged in 
Chicago with robbing a limousine driver of $130. 
</P>
<P>
Lilley, 37, of Austin, Tex., was in Chicago last week doing personal 
appearances for Halloween and was arrested Friday. Police said no weapons were 
involved and that Lilley, who used the stage name Butch Patrick as a child 
actor, was arrested along with another man who was also charged with robbery. 
Police said the two men were riding in the limo and allegedly robbed the driver 
during a stop at a service station. CLAUDIA PUIG 
