<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tuning In WKRP Again: Hugh Wilson, the creator and executive producer of the 
situation comedy "WKRP in Cincinnati," will supervise the creation and oversee 
the casting, writing and production of the new version of "WKRP" set to begin 
production this spring. 
</P>
<P>
The series, which will air next fall, will be produced by MTM Enterprises, 
which produced the first series. Also, Wilson will direct the first episode. 
The new show will feature several of the cast members from the first show, 
including Richard Sanders, Frank Bonner and Gordon Jump. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
