<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Africa's sports federations agreed to unite in support of non-racial 
sport, as well as the end of apartheid, in order to be readmitted to the 
Olympics for the first time in three decades. 
</P>
<P>
Meeting in Harare, Zimbabwe, for two days with Africa's Olympic officials, 
nearly 50 South African sports administrators pledged to work to end apartheid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
