<P>
3 EX-CAPTIVE FRENCH SOLDIERS FLY HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAIRO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three French military personnel captured recently near the Saudi-Iraqi border 
while on a scouting mission arrived in Paris early Sunday after Iraq handed 
them over to the French Embassy in Baghdad, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The three, a captain and two noncommissioned officers, were in a jeep on a 
reconnaissance patrol when they bumped into Iraqi troops. No shots were fired, 
the French army said. 
</P>
<P>
"It is not clear yet if they will face charges and punishment for allowing 
themselves to be captured," a French diplomat in the Middle East said. 
</P>
<P>
The incident, a week ago, embarrassed Paris when Iraq revealed it Friday and 
then said it was freeing them in appreciation of a special relationship with 
France. 
</P>
