<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; 
</P>
<P>
TRUCE DECLARED AT APARTMENT COMPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents and management at the Lincoln/Moody apartments have announced a truce 
less than a month after tenants publicly complained about conditions at the 
apartment complex. 
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the council meeting last week, resident Brad Barnette said that 
owners of the property had solved all the problems. 
</P>
<P>
"I think it is a moot issue at this point," Barnette said. "Everything has been 
taken care of. We are very pleased, especially with the maintenance." 
</P>
<P>
On Oct. 9, a group of tenants came to the City Council asking for help. They 
complained about unsafe stairways, lack of running water and cockroach 
infestations. 
</P>
<P>
The council investigated and gave the owner, California South West Management 
of Santa Monica, until Nov. 2 to address the complaints. 
</P>
<P>
Milton Yates, an attorney representing the owner, said he thought most of the 
cited conditions had been dealt with. "Maybe with the exception of the 
balconies," he said. Some residents' balconies had been propped up with wooden 
beams for added security. Yates said the balconies would not collapse, as 
residents had feared. 
</P>
</TEXT>
