<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Classical East Indian dancer Ramya Harishankar of Irvine has applied for a 
listing on the Touring Artists Directory of the California Arts Council. The 
council will reimburse performing arts organizations in the state that present 
artists on the roster in the 1992-93 and 1993-94 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
Harishankar, director of the Arpana Dance Company, would tour as a soloist. She 
was the only Orange County artist to apply for the support. Last year, none 
did. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County chapter of the American Institute of Architects has elected 
Dan Heinfeld of Irvine as president, succeeding Dell H. DeRevere of Newport 
Beach. Roberta W. Jorgensen of Mission Viejo is the new vice 
president/president-elect, and Howard L. Gilpin of Costa Mesa is the new chief 
financial officer. 
</P>
