<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nobody won the $4.8-million jackpot in the latest "Lotto 6-53" game, and 
lottery officials said today that Wednesday's prize could reach $9 million. 
</P>
<P>
Because no player picked all six numbers, the $4.8-million prize will roll over 
to Wednesday night's drawing. Lottery officials expected that six-of-six 
jackpot to reach $9 million. 
</P>
<P>
There were five tickets with five numbers plus the bonus number that won 
$110,611 apiece. The tickets were purchased in Burbank, Hawthorne, Los Angeles 
and two in Daly City. 
