</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A powerful homemade bomb exploded outside a Van Nuys liquor store late Sunday 
night, hurling shrapnel that shattered windows and damaged a parked car, Los 
Angeles police said today. 
</P>
<P>
The bomb had been placed on top of a pay telephone outside Adam's Liquor in a 
mini-mall at 14556 Vanowen St. and blew up about 11:30 p.m., Detective Don 
Tabak said. 
</P>
<P>
The blast blew out most of the windows of the liquor store, a restaurant and a 
video store, Tabak said. The damaged car was parked in the mini-mall parking 
lot. 
</P>
<P>
The stores were closed, and there were no injuries. A clerk at Adam's Liquor 
said that the inside of the store escaped damage and that all the businesses in 
the mini-mall are open today. 
</P>
<P>
Police had no motive or suspects in the bombing. 
</P>
