JAPANESE ALL-STARS BEAT U.S. TEAM 2-1, FOR THIRD STRAIGHT VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Makoto Sasaki of the Daiei Hawks singled home the go-ahead run in the eighth 
inning off Cincinnati's Rob Dibble to lead the Japanese all-stars past the 
major leaguers 2-1 today for their third consecutive victory in the eight-game 
goodwill series. 
</P>
<P>
